The Vice President expressed her excitement and gratitude for being in Ghana and acknowledged the international reputation of the artists and their work. She highlighted the significant impact of the creative work happening in Ghana and how it is changing the way people enjoy themselves and express their emotions. The Vice President also emphasized the universal language of music and how the artists in Ghana are speaking to people globally through their songs rooted in concepts like freedom and self-determination. She thanked the artists for their courage and sacrifice in pursuing their art and acknowledged the joy they bring to people worldwide. The Vice President also mentioned that she was accompanied by Sheryl Lee Ralph and Idris Elba, and invited Sheryl Lee to share a few words as an extraordinary artist.